HEADWORD: Frumenty
<hw>Fru"men*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>froment⟦eacute⟧e</ets>, fr. L. <ets>frumentum</ets>. See
<er>Frumentaceous</er>.]</ety> <def>Food made of hulled wheat boiled in
milk, with sugar, plums, etc.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>furmenty</asp> and <asp>furmity</asp>.]</altsp>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

